related_csets.codeset_intention: ARDS or Severe Respiratory Distress endpoint measurement concepts for ARIScience COVID research
Clinical Focus: The purpose of this value set is to represent concepts for diagnoses of pregnancy.
related_csets.limitations: The medication or test related concepts are not included. For peer reviewed phenotype for pregnancy, please refer to N3C pregnancy team's work.
related_csets.provenance: Create broad and generic general use concept as starting place for research teams with regards to Pregnancy diagnosis codes and complications. Diagnosis codes were reviewed with Pregnancy team and complications codes were added later. The use of the concept set is for risk factor related analysis.

related_csets.codeset_intention: Clinical Focus: The purpose of this value set is to represent concepts for a diagnosis of immunocompromising and chronic respiratory conditions, which increase susceptibility of contracting an acute bacterial infection., Data Element Scope: This value set may use a model element related to Diagnosis.
related_csets.limitations: Exclusion Criteria: Excludes concepts that represent a diagnosis that is not associated with increased susceptibility of contracting an acute bacterial infection.

related_csets.codeset_intention: ARDS or Severe Respiratory Distress endpoint measurement concepts for ARIScience COVID research

Clinical Focus: The purpose of this value set is to represent concepts for a diagnosis of immunocompromising and chronic respiratory conditions, which increase susceptibility of contracting an acute bacterial infection., Data Element Scope: This value set may use a model element related to Diagnosis.
related_csets.limitations: Exclusion Criteria: Excludes concepts that represent a diagnosis that is not associated with increased susceptibility of contracting an acute bacterial infection.

BLD contains 10 categories that include diseases related to the blood, diseases of blood-forming organs, and certain disorders involving the immune mechanism such as nutritional anemia, sickle cell/trait anemia, and immunity disorders.
related_csets.limitations: The grouping is based on Clinical Classifications Software Refines (CCSR). The CCSR for ICD10CM provides a method for aggregating the diagnosis codes into over 530 clinical categories across 21 body systems.  For more information about the CCSR: https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/toolssoftware/ccsr/DXCCSR-User-Guide-v2022-1.pdf

related_csets.codeset_intention: Clinical Focus: The purpose of this value set is to represent concepts for a diagnosis of immunocompromising and chronic respiratory conditions, which increase susceptibility of contracting an acute bacterial infection., Data Element Scope: This value set may use a model element related to Diagnosis.
related_csets.limitations: Exclusion Criteria: Excludes concepts that represent a diagnosis that is not associated with increased susceptibility of contracting an acute bacterial infection.

related_csets.codeset_intention: Create broad and generic general use concept as starting place for research teams and for use in calculating comorbidity indices.

related_csets.update_message: The concept set CCI-CDC Chronic Lung Disease - JS was created in Atlas (#2753) and is meant to include both the Charlson comorbidity (COPD) and the CDC list of Chronic Lung Diseases that make one more likely to get severely ill from COVID-19 according to https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/need-extra-precautions/people-with-medical-conditions.html.

related_csets.codeset_intention: ARDS or Severe Respiratory Distress endpoint measurement concepts for ARIScience COVID research

Clinical Focus: This value set identifies patients with a diagnosis of chronic obstructive pulmonary disorder (COPD).; Data Element Scope: This value set was intended to map to the QDM data type of diagnosis, but has the potential to be used in additional ways.; Inclusion Criteria: This value set includes acute COPD exacerbations, and end stage COPD. It also includes mild through severe COPD classifications.
related_csets.limitations: Exclusion Criteria: This value set excludes concurrent infections. It also excludes diagnoses of bronchitis, bronchiolitis, and emphysema.
